# Frontend Conventions

- Sections live in `src/components/sections/`; keep one job per section.
- Prefer **Server Components** for static/content sections. Use `'use client'` only for hooks, forms, canvas, or live fetches.
- Scroll animations: wrap content in `src/components/ui/FadeIn.tsx` instead of making the whole section a client component.
- Lazy-load heavy client islands from `page.tsx` with `next/dynamic` (canvas, GitHub, projects, contact, admin).
- Canvas: respect `prefers-reduced-motion`, pause when the tab is hidden, scale particle count by viewport.
- Defer below-fold network fetches until the section is near the viewport (IntersectionObserver).
- Preserve the terminal / cybersecurity visual language (mono + Space Grotesk, neon accents).
- Prefer reading admin JSON via `readJsonFile` in Server Components (or API for client islands) — avoid duplicate hard-coded copies.
- Static narrative blocks (CTF, labs, proof-of-work, timeline) may import `@/data/*.ts` directly.
- Admin UI (`AdminControls`, `AdminDashboard`) is owner-only; gate visibility on `/api/admin/check`.
- Do not add generic card grids or purple SaaS styling that fights the existing theme.
- `src/app/page.tsx` stays a Server Component; compose client islands inside it.
